Gunmen have abducted Chris Oghojafor, a final year student of the Delta State University, Abraka. The student of industrial chemistry was reportedly abducted on Friday night, April 22 in Abraka, Ethiope-East Local Government Area of the state. Daily Post reported that the gunmen demanded a ransom of N50m to secure the release of the student. The victim’s father, a Senior Legislative Aide to the Deputy Senate President, John Oghojafor Esq, revealed that the kidnappers called his wife to demand the N50m ransom, but later negotiated to N3m He said, “They kidnapped my son on Friday night. They called my wife to demand N50million. Later, they negotiated to N3 million.” Oghojafor, who made an appeal to the kidnappers to release his son unhurt, noted that Chri was just a student who was planning to be a better person in society.